Tuition fees for computer science

The tuition fees for the Faculty of Computing and Information Sciences for the 2025-2026 academic year are as follows:

- Category C (before academic scholarships): 146,540 EGP
- Category B (after partial academic scholarship): 129,300 EGP
- Category A (after partial academic scholarship): 103,440 EGP
- Non-Egyptian students: 7,500 USD

More details can be found here: [Tuition Fees](https://eui.edu.eg/tuition-fees).
Tuition fees for computer science for egyptians

For the 2025-2026 academic year, the tuition fees for Egyptian students in the Faculty of Computing and Information Sciences are as follows:

- Category A: 103,440 EGP (for students with scores of 90% or more)
- Category B: 129,300 EGP (for students with scores between 80% and less than 90%)
- Category C: 146,540 EGP (before academic scholarships)

Additionally, the tuition fees include medical insurance and are subject to annual increases. For more details on fees and scholarships, visit [Tuition Fees](https://eui.edu.eg/tuition-fees).
How to apply

To apply for financial aid at Egypt University of Informatics (EUI), you need to send an email to [financial.aid@eui.edu.eg](mailto:financial.aid@eui.edu.eg). This program is available for existing students facing significant financial challenges, and applications will be evaluated by a dedicated committee. For more details on the rules and regulations of the financial aid program, please refer to this link: [Financial Aid Program](https://eui.edu.eg/financial-aid).
